bilingual.source: Betty pulled a leaf off a plant.
bilingual.target: 贝蒂从植物上摘了一片叶子。

bilingual.source: I'm going to find the right leaf!
The book says there's a special kind of leaf.
bilingual.target: 书上说有一种特别的叶子。

bilingual.source: The water will rise up to the Leaf through the Stem.
bilingual.target: 水将通过茎上升到叶子。

bilingual.source: Then workers in the Leaf will mix water, CO and sunlight.
bilingual.target: 然后叶子中的工人将混合水、二氧化碳和阳光。

bilingual.source: Water from the root will travel to the leaf through the stem.
bilingual.target: 水从根部通过茎流向叶子。

bilingual.source: He holds a palm leaf in his hand.
bilingual.target: 他手里握着一片棕榈叶。

list.abstract: Leaf会社是AQUAPLUS旗下开发及发售十八禁游戏的厂商和品牌，在大阪淀川区和东京都有办公室。Leaf也被叫做“叶子（叶っぱ）”、“叶”。因为受了2CH「Leaf,Key」板的影响，所以和key（通称“键”）一起被归类为“叶键”。Leaf饭有时候被称为“叶派”，而key饭则被称为“键子”。

yingyinNormal.en: Dumbo Ma. That's not a leaf. Leaves are green.
yingyinNormal.zh: 傻瓜妈妈，这才不是树叶，叶子是绿色的。

yingyinNormal.en: What we want to do is just slice long thin strips like this. Wrap one Chinese cabbage leaf around each meatball.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们只需要切开像这样切成细长条，在每个肉丸边放一片大白菜叶。

yingyinNormal.en: There's a leaf. Do you see that? Where? Look. I don't see a leaf.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里有片树叶，你看见了吗？在哪？看。我没看到树叶。

yingyinNormal.en: The silica is built into row upon row of tiny daggers along the leaf.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这种硅物质组成了叶片边缘，鳞次栉比的小小利齿。

yingyinNormal.en: It's actually all to do with something that coats the edge of the leaf.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实际上这和叶片边缘表层有关。

yingyinNormal.en: It's something almost invisible tucked away inside the leaf of a plant.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这项演变深藏于植物叶片之内并不易为人所知。

yingyinNormal.en: Magnify a leaf 1,000 times and you can see them. They're known as chloroplasts. Packed into every cell.
yingyinNormal.zh: 将叶片放大一千倍 便一目了然，我们称其为叶绿体，在每个细胞中都充斥着叶绿体。

yingyinNormal.en: You okay? Oh! Yeah. Yeah, I was just sitting here and this leaf blew in. You ever see a color like this?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你还好吗？哦！好啊。我刚才坐在这里，然后这片叶子飘了进来，你见过这样的颜色吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Inside every leaf of every plant on the planet are the direct descendants of those first green bacteria.
yingyinNormal.zh: 地球上每株植物的每片叶子之中，都排满了绿细菌鼻祖的直系后代。

yingyinNormal.en: Sometimes it's okay to just be a leaf in the wind and see where we land. Even when we don't like what's happening to us?
yingyinNormal.zh: 有时做一片随风飞舞不知落向何处的树叶也没什么，即使我们不喜欢发生的这些事情？

yingyinNormal.en: In examining this new pressure-sensitive adhesive, I found more Dutch Gold Leaf.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对这个新的压敏胶黏剂进行试验之后，我发现了更多的荷兰金箔。

yingyinNormal.en: Starting tomorrow, I am turning over a new leaf. Time with you is my number one priority.
yingyinNormal.zh: 明天起我会重新做人，和你在一起才是头等大事。

yingyinNormal.en: The same imitation gold leaf from the Chagall frame? That is correct. And there was nothing else.
yingyinNormal.zh: 跟夏加尔画框上的人造金箔是一样的吗？是的，而且除了金箔外没有别的东西了。

yingyinNormal.en: Lovely. Next I'm going to add in fried tofu, fresh tofu, and some Chinese leaf, just to soak up all those flavors.
yingyinNormal.zh: 接下来放入油豆腐，新鲜豆腐，还有大白菜，它们能吸收所有的味道。

examination_example.sentence: A frequent presence of petals or <highlight>leaves</highlight> as well as of stuffed animals.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 经常出现的花瓣、树叶以及毛绒玩具。
